<doc id="176139" wikidata="Q710022" url="?curid=176139" title="Lierneux">
<text>Lierneux (; ) is a municipality of Wallonia located in the province of Liège, Belgium. 

On January 1, 2006, Lierneux had a total population of 3,367. The total area is 92.08 km2 which gives a population density of 37 inhabitants per km2. Lierneux is known for its psychiatric hospital CHS l&#x27;Accueil.

The municipality consists of the following districts: Arbrefontaine, and Bra, and Lierneux.

==History==
Within the bounds of the municipality a lies a memorial site to the tribute of the 82nd Airborne Division who won the Battle of the Bulge against the German SS division December 22, 1944.

